<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Encourages Foreign Investment in Hydel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Pakistani government will
announce some lucrative incentives soon to attract foreign
investment in the country's hydel power sector instead of thermal
sector, official sources said today.
</P>
<P>
The government had recently directed the Board of Investment to
discourage further foreign investment in the thermal sector and
refrain from signing any new thermal power generation pact, said
the sources in the Ministry of Investment.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the government wanted to alleviate the
import bill of fuel, which is consumed in bulk by the thermal
power projects, and the only way to do this is to discourage
further investment in this sector.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the country's northern areas are good for developing
hydel power projects, where small dams can be built easily to
generate cheaper energy, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
