<HEADLINE> 10 Killed in Traffic Accidents in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and
three injured in two separates traffic accidents in India today,
Press Trust of India reported.
</P>
<P>
Five people were killed and three others injured when their
jeep collided with a truck in the Rajasthan State today, local
police department said.
</P>
<P>
In another accident in Uttar Pradesh today, five people were
killed when a truck overturned.
</P>
<P>
Twelve people were aboard the fruit-laden truck when the
tragedy took place.  
</P>
</TEXT>
