<HEADLINE> Mexico Wins First Gold at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Dennise Lopez Sing of
Mexico won her country the first gold medal at the on-going World
University Games by taking the women's vault title here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Lopez Sing's winning results is 9.437 points, followed by Alla
Plechkova of Russia in the second place at 9.262 points.
</P>
<P>
Leah Brown of the United States claimed the bronze medal with
9.237 points. 
</P>
