<HEADLINE> Zheng Zhi Wins Women's Uneven Bars Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Zheng Zhi of China took the
gold medal of the women's uneven bars at the Universiade on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Zheng, the fourth placed gymnast in last night's women's all-around
competitions, was superb in the competitions today and collected 9.650
points for the gold medal.
</P>
<P>
Risa Sugawara of Japan finished second at 9.400 points, followed by
Kathleen Shrieves of the United States for the bronze medal at 9.225
points. 
</P>
