<HEADLINE> British Jet Makes Emergency Landing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A holiday jet carring 183 British
tourists made an emergency landing at London's Gatwick airport
today and partially left the runway after suffering hydraulic
problems.
</P>
<P>
The Airtours International Boeing B-757 blocked the airport's
runway for almost three hours, causing delays. Everyone on board
left the plane safely using the emergency chutes, an airline
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The plane was 50 minutes into its flight to Majorca when the
pilot noticed a warning light on the instrument panel.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time in four days that the airline's planes
had been involved in an emergency. On Thursday the pilot of an
Airtours B-757 aborted a take-off from Glasgow airport after a
bird was sucked into one of the engines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
