<HEADLINE> Italian Hero Juri Chechi Takes Rings Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Italian hero Juri Chechi
gave Italy the first gold medal at the 1997 World University Games
after winning the rings event at the gymnastics tournament here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Chechi, an Olympic champion of the event, was awarded 9.800 points,
the highest score so far in Sunday's compeitions.
</P>
<P>
Robert Galli of Italy finished second at 9.650 points. Igor Ivanov
of Russia and Aleksej Demjanov of Croatia shared the bronze medal at
9.600. 
</P>
