<HEADLINE> Iraq's Cabinet Reshuffled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, August 24 (Xinhua) -- In a cabinet reshuffle today,
Iraqi President Saddam Hussein named three new ministers and
sacked Minister of Culture and Information Hamed Youssef Hammadi.
</P>
<P>
Hammam Abdul-Khalek, former minister of higher education and
scientific research, was appointed the new cultural minister.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time for Hammadi to be removed from the
portfolio in two years. He was reappointed minister of culture and
information in October 1996 after being sacked in January the same
year.
</P>
<P>
Abdul-Gabbar Tawfiq, former minister of education, was
appointed minister of higher education and scientific research.
</P>
<P>
Fahd Salem Al-Shokrah, a leading member of the ruling Ba'ath
party, was appointed minister of education, the Iraqi News Agency
(INA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The INA gave no details on the reasons for the removal of
Hammadi.
</P>
<P>
Saddam Hussein presided today over a cabinet meeting during
which he stressed the importance of effective administration by
ministers and their aides. 
</P>
