<HEADLINE> Japan, China Take More Gymnastic Golds at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Italy, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Japanese Gymnasts who will
compete in the forthcoming world championships, won five out of
today's 11 gold medals at the Universiade gymnastic competiton which
closed at the Sports Center here on Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
Japanese girl Risa Sugawara won two gold medals, snatching the
floor exercise and beam champions with respective 9.675 and 9.500
points, her compatriot Naoya Tsukahara scored 9.375 points for the
men's vault gold, Yoshihiro Saito took high bar title with 9.400
points, Japan's Kenichi Fujita and Romania's Ioan Suciu have shared
the pommel horse gold with an identical score of 9.650 points.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Gymnasts took three gold medals. ZHao Sheng scored 9.600
points for the parallel bars champion and won the floor exercise title
with 9.450 points, and Zheng Zhi grabbed the women's uneven bars gold
with 9.650 points.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Atlanta Olympic rings champion Jury Chechi recorded 9.800
points for rings gold and Dennise Lopez Sing of Mexico won the
women's vault tital with 9.437 points.
</P>
<P>
At the four-day gymnastics competition, both China and Japan
picked up five gold medals each. The United States and Russia also
won one gold respectively.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhennan, manager of the Chinese gymnastic team, said that many
countries are preparing the coming world championships and they didn't
send their national team to the Universiade. Only few countries
including Japan and South Korea have sent their best team to the games.
</P>
<P>
Ye added that our young gymnasts did better in the games and took
more gold medals than the past Universiade. " It is the first time for
the Chinese gymnasts to win the men's team title and take the men's
individual all-around champion at the Universiade," he concluded.
</P>
</TEXT>
