<HEADLINE> Japan Take Half Gold of Gymnastics Apparatus Competitions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Empty-handed Japan suddenly
got full-handed with five gold medals through their gymnasts on the
last day of the Universiade gymnastics tournament on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Risa Sugawara, who finished third in Friday's women's individual
all-around final, won the titles of the floor exercise and balance
beam.
</P>
<P>
Her compatriots Yoshihiro Saito took the men's horizontal bar title
while Kenichi Fujita and Naoya Tsukahara added one each to Japan's
gold tally by winning the men's pommel horse and vault events
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Before today's apparatus finals, Japan had only one silver and two
bronze medals to their credit. But now they are second in the gold
medal table only after leaders Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
On Sunday morning, Elena Vitrichenko of Ukraine won three more gold
medals in the rhythmic gymnastics, becoming the first multi gold
medalist of the Universiade.
</P>
<P>
In the evening's men's individual epee final, Alexander Gorbachuk
edged Cuban Ivan Trevejo 16-15 to give Ukraine their sixth gold medal
at the games.
</P>
<P>
The victory in fencing promoted Ukraine to top of the medal table
with 6 golds, followed by China and Japan with 5 each.
</P>
<P>
China got three more golds in gymnastics through Zhao Sheng and
Zheng Zhi. Zhao Sheng won the titles in men's floor exercise and
parallel bars while Zheng Zhi took the gold of the women's uneven
bars.
</P>
<P>
But China's soccer team suffered another early exit as they lost to
Ukraine 2-0 in the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time in two months that China's youth eleven
failed to achieve good results in important international tournament.
</P>
<P>
In the world youth championships held in Malaysia in June, the same
Chinese team had two draws against one loss in group competitions and
failed to enter the quarter-finals.
</P>
<P>
Hosts Italy proved that they are the favorities for the soccer
title after beating the Netherlands 4-0.
</P>
<P>
The United States also scored a big victory, beating their Irish
opponents 5-0 to enter the semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The biggest victory for Italy of the day was a gold from the rings
of gymnastics taken by their Hero Juri Chechi.
</P>
<P>
Chechi, Olympic champion of the event, didn't take part in the
individual all-around competitions held last night.
</P>
<P>
His 9.800 winning score brought Italy their first gold since the
opening of the 19th World University Games on August 19.
</P>
<P>
Mexico also got their first gold in the games when Dennise Lopez
Sing won the title of the women's vault at 9.437 points.
</P>
<P>
The American gymnasts, who finished one-two in Friday's women's
individual all-around final, got only one bronze through Leah Brown in
the women's vault.
</P>
<P>
Shannon Miller, seven-time Olympic medalist, failed to shine again
in the apparatus finals. The sole gold she won at the games is the
women's individual all-around.
</P>
<P>
The diving tournament of the games will open tomorrow at Messina,
one of the three cities playing host to the games.
</P>
<P>
The diving tournament features eight events, including men's and
women's 1-meter and 3-meter springboard, men's and women's platform
and men's and women's team events. 
</P>
</TEXT>
