<HEADLINE> Nepalese Man Murders Mother, Brother With Incantations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Police in Banke district of
mid-western Nepal have arrested a man for beating his brother and
mother to death in the name of reviving them by the Shamanism
incantations, the official RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Birendra Murau, who is said to have learnt the art of Shamanism
from an Indian hermit, tried to revive his suddenly-fainting
younger brother with Shamanism incantations on August 20.
</P>
<P>
Shamanism is the belief in the world of spirits and Shamans,
who, it is believed, work in the world of spirits while in a
dreamlike state for the purpose of curing the sick and gaining
important knowledge.
</P>
<P>
In the process he severely beat his brother to death, the RSS
said.
</P>
<P>
The mother fainted at seeing her younger son's tragic death.
</P>
<P>
Murau, thinking that his mother was possessed by the dead soul
and evil spirit, tried again to revive her by applying the same
practice, finally leading to another death, the agency said.
</P>
</TEXT>
