<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Machinery Industry More Capable of Equipping Nat'l Economy (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China's machine-building
industry has geared up its operation to the market economy and
thus become more powerful to support the national economic
development, according to a top official in charge of the industry.
</P>
<P>
Bao Xuding, minister of the machine-building industry, recently
told Xinhua that the Chinese government has designated the
machine-building and automobile industries as two of the economic
pillars in the Ninth Five-Year Plan (1996-2000).
</P>
<P>
"China's huge market demand provides a good opportunity to the
development of the machine-building industry," Bao said.
</P>
<P>
According to a report of the Ministry of Machine-building
Industry (MMI), 70 percent of the investment in China's auto
industry, and half of the total poured in its electronic industry
and thermal power plants construction in the Ninth Five-Year Plan
period will be used to purchase machinery products.
</P>
<P>
Of the huge capitals to be used by the Three Gorges Project,
China's largest ever hydro-power project, some 35 percent will go
to the procurement of machinery products.
</P>
<P>
To meet the market demand, the industry in the past five years
has tried every effort to build up an operation system catering to
the market economy.
</P>
<P>
Bao said that since 1992 China has developed over 600 new
products, of which 200 could match the international level.
</P>
<P>
China now is capable of producing over 160 large complete plant
equipment, including 300mw and 600mw thermal power generating
units, 500kv power transmission and tranforming equipment and
drillers for digging 6000-meter deep oil wells in desert.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Machinery Industry More Capable of Equipping Nat'l Economy (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The output of certain machinery products, such as power
generating equipment and machine tools have been among the
world's biggest.
</P>
<P>
Its auto production has topped 1.49 million units in 1996,
doubled that the figure in 1991.
</P>
<P>
As for the central tasks in the coming years, the ministry
plans to develop 1,000 famous brand-names, 500 quality-prestigeous
enterprises and a complete quality-warranty system.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the ministry hoped to optimize its industrial
structure by fostering 100 large enterprises and a contingent of
professional parts and components suppliers "competitive in the
marketplace," according to the minister.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises are urged to put greater efforts on research and
development as well as sales and marketing besides enhancing their
processing capabilities, Bao added.
</P>
<P>
Bao emphasized the importance of the research and development
efforts. "The ministry plans to establish development centers in
300 key enterprises and develop 1000 competitive and patent
products in the years ahead," Bao said.
</P>
<P>
The industry witnessed a rapid growth in the past five years by
registering an annual growth of 22.4 percent, "becoming one of the
fastest-growing industries in China," according to Bao.
</P>
<P>
The output value of the industry last year hit 1,398.7 billion
yuan, or 25 percent of the country's total, up four percentage
points than that in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The industry earned an aggregated tax and profits of 391.2
billion yuan in the past five years, up 102 percent
compared than that registered between 1986 and 1990.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the ministry attracted the contractual
overseas investment totaling 20 billion US dollars, rising
tenfold than the amount combined before 1991.
</P>
<P>
The export volume of machinery products totaled more than 100
billion dollars between 1992 and 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
