<HEADLINE> Hot Autumn in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- High temperatures continue in
Beijing these days after a rarely-seen hot Summer over the past
few decades.
</P>
<P>
The summit temperatures in the urban area of Beijing have reached
33 degrees or over, centigrade, in the past three days, after the
Beginning of Autumn (13th solar term) happened about 20 days ago.
</P>
<P>
"Beijing is sleepless because of the hot weather this Autumn,
and we are hoping that it will go quickly," a local resident
complains.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has always been well known for its cool autumn,
however, this fall is a surprise for local residents.
</P>
<P>
All the paging service sations have been repeating the same
news about the hot weather, and warning millions of their
subscribers not to catch sunstroke.
</P>
<P>
The city now is absolutely under control of subtropical high
pressure, and it seems that hot and wet temperatures will go on
for several days, according to weather forecast.
</P>
<P>
What makes this autumn more unbearable is the increasing air
humidity, which hit 90 percent at the highest level.
</P>
<P>
But it turns out to be a good season for air conditioner
sellers, who have seen a continued brisk sale of air conditioners
after the hot summer. Some departments stores have sold out their
stocks for next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
