<HEADLINE> Bing Xin Literary Center Inaugurated in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Literary Center to mark the
great literary achievements of Bing Xin, a famous female Chinese
writer, was inaugurated today in Changle, her hometown in east
China's Fujian Province.
</P>
<P>
Bing Xin, who personally witnessed almost all major historical
events in the country for nearly a century, enjoys a reputation as
"the grandmother of literary circles." Her works have greatly
influenced Chinese readers for generations and are considered the
cultural wealth of the country.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the center commenced in July last year and was
completed this May. The complex, which covers 4,414 sq.m,, was
built at a cost of 7.8 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
The center complex, which includes exhibition halls, a research
center and offices, was built to display the writer's literary
works and lifelong achievements.  
</P>
