<HEADLINE> ASEAN Plans to Help Cambodia Prepare Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Indonesian Foreign Minister Ali
Alatas today reaffirmed the ASEAN's readiness to help Cambodia
prepare its general election in next May and urged the Cambodian
parliament to draw up election regulations soon.
</P>
<P>
"ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) realizes that
the implementation of a general election needs elaborate
preparations. Thus, election regulations are very important," the
minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said ASEAN will discuss the plan on helping Cambodia prepare
its general election, in New York next month when ministers of the
grouping attend the United Nations General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
"Perhaps I will meet with (Cambodian newly-appointed First
Prime Minister and Foreign Minister) Ung Huot and discuss the
issue with him (in New York)," Alatas said.
</P>
<P>
On Cambodia's election, Alatas said ASEAN supports Cambodian
Second Prime Minister Hun Sen's commitment to organize a free and
constitutional election.
</P>
<P>
"We should support his commitment to hold that kind of
election," he said.
</P>
<P>
He added that Cambodia's chance to become a full member of
ASEAN would depend much on the country's internal situation and
security.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN foreign ministers in July decided to postpone Cambodia's
entry into the grouping because of the political crisis in the
country but maintain its observer status.
</P>
<P>
Alatas also called on Cambodia's disputing parties to halt
immediately all military actions to avoid being trapped in armed
conflict.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar,
the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
