<HEADLINE> Large Number of AIDS Patients Registered in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- AIDS patients reached 78,000
last year in Cameroon's North West Province with a population of
1.19 million, a provincial health official has revealed.
</P>
<P>
Amida Ghogomu, the provincial delegate of public health, made
the revelation in the province's capital Bamenda recently while
opening a two-day AIDS education workshop for youths and student
leaders from the seven divisions of the North West Province,
local paper "Cameroon Tribune" reported today.
</P>
<P>
AIDS cases have increased geometrically from the prevalence of
0.02 percent in 1985 to that of seven percent in 1996, that is
about 78,000 persons infected, with youths accounting for 60
percent of that figure, the report said.
</P>
<P>
This rate is higher than the average prevalence of 5.5 percent
throughout the whole territory.
</P>
<P>
Ghogomu pointed out that the objective of the workshop is to
give the youths necessary information, guidance and skills that
will reduce the incidence of sexually transmitted diseases (STD),
unwanted pregnancies and consequent drop-out from school among
students.
</P>
<P>
He assured that the workshop participants will be assisted
financially to succeed in their individual sensitization programs
in their respective villages and communities, adding that
follow-up teams will visit various youths and student
associations soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
