<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Stresses Importance of Basic Scientific Research (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
recently stressed the importance of basic scientific research,
saying that major breakthroughs in this respect will play an
inestimable roles in promoting the progress of science and
technology, as well as the economy and culture.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who also serves as General Secretary of the Central
Committee of the Chinese Communist Party (CPC), made the remarks
in written instructions concerning the Summary of the Third
Session of the State Science and Technology Leading Group.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese president noted that the modern history of mankind
has fully proved that major breakthroughs in basic scientific
research are of incalculable importance to enhancing the ability
of people to understand and transform the world.
</P>
<P>
China has gained worldwide acknowledgement to important
achievements in the basic scientific research since the founding
of new China in 1949, particularly since the start of the reform
and opening drive in 1978, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's limited financial ability prevents it
from simultaneously focusing extensive efforts on all areas,
according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the country should accelerate basic scientific
research from a comprehensive standpoint based on order of
importance and urgency. Related efforts should be carried out in
accordance with needs of long-term social and economic development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang added that the country must reform its scientific and
technological system and adopt favorable policies to support and
encourage enterprises to engage in scientific research,
development and technological transformations.
</P>
</TEXT>
