<HEADLINE> Chinese, Singaporean PMs Satisfied with Bilateral Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese Premier Li
Peng and Singapore Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong reviewed here
today the development of the Sino-Singapore relations in recent
years and expressed their satisfaction with the fruitful
cooperation between the two countries in all fields.
</P>
<P>
During their discussion, held in the Presidential Palace
Istana, Li Peng noted that in the seven years since the
establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries,
bilateral ties have developed rapidly, featuring frequent exchange
of visits by top-level leaders and increased bilateral trade and
investment.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation between China and Singapore is now witnessing new
development in telecommunication, civil aviation and other hi-tech
areas, Li said.
</P>
<P>
He also appreciated the mutual understanding and support
between China and Singapore over many important international and
regional issues.
</P>
<P>
Agreeing with Li Peng, Prime Minister Goh said that the two
countries are enjoying very good relations. Given the fact that
there is no pending issues between the two countries, Goh said
that Singapore and China should further expand their cooperation,
especially in the construction of the Singapore-Suzhou Industrial
Park, the flagship project in Singapore's economic regionalization
drive.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that since this is a long-term project, the two
countries should continue to make joint efforts to make this
important project successful.
</P>
<P>
The two Prime Ministers agreed that it is necessary for leaders
of the two countries to continue to keep in contact and dialogue
so as to push bilateral cooperation into the fields of health,
culture and education, and tourism.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also stressed that the two nations will
continue to maintain constant consultation and coordination
between them and work together to make contribution to promoting
regional peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
On the economic and trade cooperation between China and
Singapore, Li Peng said that currently, the subject the two
countries should study is how to make full use of their respective
advantage and expand the area of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Highlighting that China is speeding up its adjustment of
industrial structure and trying to raise its technological
standards, Li said that Singapore can surely play a more active
role in China's economic development, given its advantage in the
fields such as information technology, management and finance.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that China's market is stable and that making
investment in China will not only bring about high returns for the
Singapore investors, but also benefit both sides.
</P>
<P>
Goh Chok Tong agreed with Li Peng and said that enterprises and
companies of the two countries should be encouraged to invest in
each other's country or join their hands to invest in third
countries.
</P>
<P>
Li also briefed his Singaporean counterpart on the state of
affairs of Hong Kong after its return to China last month. He said
that Hong Kong and the Southeast Asian region are closely linked.
It is to the benefit of Southeast Asian countries that prosperity
and stability in Hong Kong are maintained.
</P>
<P>
Goh said that Singapore has always been supportive to Hong
Kong's return to China. He said he was glad to see that everything
goes well in Hong Kong after its return.
</P>
<P>
Singapore has invested heavily in Hong Kong and will continue
to do so in the future, he said, adding that Singapore is fully
confident in Hong Kong's continued prosperity and stability.
</P>
<P>
On the relations between China and the Association of South
East Asian Nations (ASEAN), the two Prime Ministers believed that
the integration of the Southeast Asian region is in conformity
with the world trend of multi-polarization, and is conducive to
long-term peace and stability in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
They held that the bilateral relations between China and ASEAN
are very important and the two sides should further strengthen
their cooperation in every field.
</P>
<P>
Noting that towards the end of this year, leaders from the
ASEAN, China, Japan and South Korea will meet in Kuala Lumpur,
Malaysia, Goh hoped that the meeting will be successful through
their joint efforts.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders also exchanged views on regional and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng arrived here on Sunday and will wind up his visit here
on Tuesday.  
</P>
</TEXT>
