<HEADLINE> Macao Airport Reports Remarkable Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Macao International Airport
reported remarkable growth in its flow of passengers and cargo in
the first six months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The Macao International Airport Company (CAM) said in a
newsletter which Xinhua received today that its passenger usage
grew 98 percent and cargo throughput increased 193 percent
compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 962,925 passengers used the airport from January to
June this year, compared with 485,257 passengers in the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The amount of cargo transported through the airport rose from
6,205 tons in the first six months of last year to 18,151 tons in
the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Inaugurated in November 1995, the airport has opened a dozen
air routes to China's inland areas, Taiwan, some Southeast Asian
nations and Europe.  
</P>
</TEXT>
