<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Substantial Progress in State Enterprise Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In line with the arrangement of the CPC Central Committee,
China has spread the experimental reforms to wider areas, making
substantial progress in some important aspects, the commentary
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Except for one being disintegrated and another one merged, 98
of the 100 enterprises selected by the State Council to establish
a modern enterprise system on a trial basis have been transformed
into companies of different types in accordance with the needs of
a modern enterprise system, it said.
</P>
<P>
The work to establish a modern enterprise system in 2,500
enterprises selected by the local governments has also gone into
full swing, with nearly half already transformed into joint-stock
companies or limited liability companies, it added.
</P>
<P>
The experiment to optimize the capital structure has expanded
to 110 from 18 cities, and 120 enterprises have been selected to
form large enterprise groups, according to the commentary.
</P>
<P>
Since last year the pace to develop and strengthen large
enterprises groups has been accelerated markedly, it said.
</P>
<P>
The 300 large enterprises that enjoy priority treatment from
the State government account for 0.44 percent of all state-owned
industrial enterprises. However, their sales income and profits
last year accounted for 43.73 percent and 65.85 percent of the
total, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The commentary said that a good match-up of internal reforms
with reform in other sectors is a major reason for the success of
the state enterprise reforms, adding that another factor is
improved management.
</P>
<P>
Though progress has been made in the state enterprise reforms,
the remaining tasks are very arduous, the commentary pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"However, the difficulties are temporary and transformation is
sure to happen," it said. "The more difficult and critical it is,
the more confident we should be about resolving the difficulties
and tiding over the difficult time." 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
