between Netanyahu and Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Israel has prevented about 100,000 Palestinians
from going to work by closing them inside the West Bank and Gaza
Strip.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu also asked for Japan's diplomatic efforts in gaining
Palestinian Authority's cooperation in fighting terrorism, the
spokesman said. Japan is one of the largest donors to the
Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
Netanyahu, who arrived in Tokyo on Sunday night, was
accompanied by his finance minister and about 20 Israeli
businessmen. 
