<HEADLINE> Indian-Pakistani Troops Continue Exchanging Fire in Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Indian and Pakistani troops
today continued exchanging heavy artillery and small arms fire
along the control line in Jammu and Kashmir, said defense ministry
sources here.
</P>
<P>
About 50 Pakistani soldiers and five Indians, including three
civilians, have been killed since last friday when heavy exchange
of fire occurred in the Kargil, Uri and Kupwara areas of Jammu and
Kashmir, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
However, a Pakistani defense ministry spokesman said in
Islamabad today that there has been no unusual activity along the
control line.
</P>
<P>
This is believed to be the second heavy exchange of fire
between Indian and Pakistani forces along the control line in the
disputed Jammu and Kashmir this year. The first incident took
place from April 9 to 13, local press reported. 
</P>
