<HEADLINE> More Stockholmers in Favour of Hosting 2004 Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Several opinion polls about
the question of bidding the 2004 Olympic Games shows that more
Stockholmers are in favour of the Games to be held in the city.
</P>
<P>
The survey, sporsored by Swedish Institute of Public Opinion
Research (SIFO), indicates that 53 percent of Stockholmers,
compared with 49 percent in May, are in favour of the Games being
held in Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
Those who are against have inclined from 40 percent in May to
34 percent.
</P>
<P>
For the whole country the figures are as follows: 50 percent
in favour while 49 percent in May, and 33 percent against, compared
with 41 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
The result of another poll is different. It shows that almost
60 percent of Stockholmers are in favour of the capital to host
the Games. Supporters in this poll believe that Sweden will not
suffer any negative economic effects from staging the Games.
</P>
<P>
But a bomb exploded in a western city of Gothenburg early
Monday has made Stockholm in danger in its Olympic bidding. The
blast with no one injured at the Ullevi stadium was the latest in
a series of explosions against Sweden's Olympic bid.
</P>
<P>
Stockholm is one of the five cities entered the final
round. The decision on the host city will be taken on September 5
in Lausanne, Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
