<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Goh: Li Peng's Visit Pushes Bilateral Ties to New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng's
ongoing visit will lift Singapore-China relations to greater
heights, Singaporean Prime Minister Goh Chok Tong said here today.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a banquet he hosted in Li's honor, Goh described Li
as his old friend and China the friend of Singapore.
</P>
<P>
He noted that since the diplomatic ties were established seven
years ago, the bilateral ties "have blossomed", with the bilateral
trade in 1996 reaching some 7.3 billion U.S. dollars and
Singapore's contractual investment in China by the third quarter
of 1996 amounting to 22 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
"But bilateral relations are more than just facts and figures,
or trade and investment," Goh said, adding "They are about human
relationship, warmth and abiding ties. Frequent face-to-face
meetings between leaders help to foster a healthy relationship
between countries."
</P>
<P>
He noted that China's economy is booming and in the past
decade, the economy has grown at an average of 10 percent a year.
</P>
<P>
If the current rates of growth are sustained, he went on,
China's GNP will be the largest in the world within 20 to 30
years.
</P>
<P>
China's international influence will grow along with its
economic strength when it contributes to global peace, stability
and prosperity, the Singaporean prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
He stated that the smooth return of Hong Kong to the motherland
was testimony to how patience, sensitivity and creative diplomacy
ensured the peaceful resolution of a difficult problem left behind
by history.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that as a special administrative region of
China, Hong Kong will continue to prosper and serve as an engine
of growth for China and the region," stressed Goh.
</P>
<P>
On the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN), Goh said
another development important to the region is ASEAN's expansion
to nine, and eventually 10 members.
</P>
<P>
He explained that the ASEAN has fostered regional economic
cooperation and enhanced regional peace, and through forums like
the ASEAN Forum, Asia-Pacific Economic Cooperation and Asia-Europe
meeting, the major powers, including China, are constructively
engaged with the ASEAN.
</P>
<P>
"Sino-ASEAN relations have developed rapidly over the last few
years. China is now a full ASEAN Dialogue partner. As ASEAN
progresses, we look forward to a friendly and beneficial
relationship with China," Goh added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
