<HEADLINE> Malaria Situation Serious in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Malaria is a major disease in
Uganda, threatening people's lives, reported mass media here
today.
</P>
<P>
The report said that malaria situation in Uganda is very
serious, noting that malaria is responsible for 25 percent of
patients attendances at health units and 14 percent of patient
deaths.
</P>
<P>
A doctor from Uganda's Communicable Disease Cont (CDC) was
quoted as saying that the Ministry of Health plans to spend more
on controlling malaria in accordance with a national policy that
involves participation at the community, district and national
levels.
</P>
<P>
Chloroquine is still Uganda's leading remedy for malaria and
the malaria control policy in Uganda favors the use of
chloroquine above any other drug, the doctor said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
