<HEADLINE> Chen Lixia Leads Diving Preliminaries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Chen Lixia of China led the
women's 1-meter springboard diving preliminaries on the opening day of
the Universiade diving tournament at Messina on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Chen, whose best result is a seventh place
finishing at the 1997 national champions cup, totalled 264.84 points
to lead a pool of 26 divers into the semi-finals to be held in the
afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Michelle Rojohn of the United States placed second with 257.43
points, followed by her fellow American Jennifer Lingamfelter in the
third place at 255.15.
</P>
<P>
Lu Haisong of China, who finished sixth at the national champions
cup, came fourth with 250.44 points.
</P>
<P>
After 5 dives in the semi-finals, the top 12 finishers will advance
into the final which will be held late on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
