<HEADLINE> Pak Public Figure on China's Role in World Arena </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 25 (Xinhua) -- "China has become a major
player in international political and economic arena due to her
rapidly increasing overall national strength," said Iftikhar Ahmed
Khan, Vice President of All Pakistan-China Friendship Association.
</P>
<P>
In a recent interview with Xinhua, the former Pakistani attache
to China spoke highly of the spectacular achievements in the
economic and diplomatic fields that China has made over the past
two decades.
</P>
<P>
Talking about China's diplomatic achievements, Iftikhar said,
"China has consistently pursued an independent foreign policy of
peace and continually strengthened economic cooperation with all
nations throughout the world on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit."
</P>
<P>
"China has also kept opposing imperialism, hegemonism and
expansionism and advocating resolution of regional disputes
through peaceful means," he said.
</P>
<P>
When dealing with the state-to-state relations, he said, China
strictly adheres to the Five Principles of mutual respect for
sovereignty and territorial integrity, mutual non-aggression,
non-interference in each other's internal affairs, equality and
mutual benefit, and peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
"It is because of her such principled diplomatic stand, China
has won the respect of the majority of the world countries,
particularly the developing countries in the international
affairs," Iftikhar said.
</P>
<P>
"With her increasing overall national strength, China will play
a more important role in international affairs, especially in
establishing a new international order of justice and equality,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
During the two decades since China put into practice the policy
of reform and opening to the outside world in 1978, Iftikhar said,
tremendous changes have taken place in China's political, economic
and social fields.
</P>
<P>
"With a stable political situation and a record economic growth
rate, China is now marching towards an economic power," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about the forthcoming 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China, Iftikhar said, "It is a major event in
the political and economic lives of Chinese people."
</P>
<P>
"During the meeting, Chinese leaders will make very important
decisions to ensure a sustained development of the country's
economy," he said. "The meeting will exert an important impact on
China's political and economic life as well as on the world as a
whole."  
</P>
</TEXT>
