<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deputies to 15th National Party Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking official of the
Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC) said here
today that the deputies to the 15th National Party Congress are
highly representative, and are key members and model workers from
all fields.
</P>
<P>
The election of the deputies began in last November in 36
costituencies throughout the country, including departments of the
CPC Central Committee and central government, the All-China
Federation of Taiwan Compatriots, the People's Liberation Army and
members of the armed police, as well as in 31 provinces,
autonomous regions and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The 36 constituencies across the nation had elected 2,049
deputies to the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of
China (CPC) by the end of June. Later, one elected deputy faced
deprivation of his deputy qualifications for seriously violating
the Party discipline.
</P>
<P>
1,554 leading officials at various levels were elected,
accounting for 75.9 percent of the total number of deputies. 494
deputies of model workers, advanced workers, outstanding experts,
and heroes from all walks of life, account for 24.1 percent, up
2.1 percent over the number for the 14th National Party
Congress. The long list includes outstanding Party members such as
Xu Hu, Xu Honggang, Li Suli and Li Guo'an.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Deputies to 15th National Party Congress (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The 344 female deputies account for 16.8 percent of the total,
up 1.1 percent over the 14th National Party Congress. 219 deputies
are from ethnic minority groups, accounting for 10.7 percent, up
0.8 percent from the previous congress.
</P>
<P>
The composition of deputies to the 15th National Party Congress
indicates that the education level of the Party members has
improved greatly along with rationalization of the age structure.
</P>
<P>
1,709 of the 2,048 deputies have received college education,
accounting for 83.5 percent of the total, up 12.7 percent over the
14th National Party Congress; 318 or 15.5 of the total have high
school education; and 21 or 1.1 percent have primary school
education.
</P>
<P>
1,301 deputies under the age of 55 account for 63.5 percent of
the total, up 4.6 percent on the previous congress.
</P>
<P>
The 1,933 deputies who joined the Party after the founding of
new China in 1949 account for 94.4 percent of the total, up 11.5
percent on the 14th National Party Congress. 756 of them joined
the Party before May, 1966; 606 joined the Party between May 1966
and October 1976; and 571 joined the Party after November 1976.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee invited 60 elderly Party members to
serve as special deputies to the 15th National Party Congress. All
of them joined the Party before 1927 and once held important
leading posts. These senior comrades enjoy high prestige and
command universal respect.
</P>
<P>
Special deputies enjoy the same rights as formally elected
deputies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
