<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese NPC Standing Committee Meeting Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The 27th Meeting of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC), China's
top legislature, opened here today, as lawmakers began to examine
draft laws on flood control, price, prevention and alleviation of
disasters caused by earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
The today's meeting was presided over by Qiao Shi, chairman of
the NPC Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi said this is the second time the draft law on flood
control is presented for discussion, and is expected to be adopted
by the NPC Standing Committee at this meeting.
</P>
<P>
When explaining the draft law on price entrusted by the State
Council, Chen Jinhua, minister in charge of the State Planning
Commission, told the lawmakers that the law aims at meeting the
demands of China's socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
"It helps establish and improve a mechanism of price formed by
the market under the macro-economic control," the minister said.
</P>
<P>
It is necessary to define the experience and practice of the
price reform over the past 18 years in order to deepen the price
reform, standardize price actions, give full play of price in a
reasonable resource disposition, stablize the overall price level,
and ensure a healthy development of a socialist market economy,
Chen said.
</P>
<P>
Chen Zhangli, director of the State Seismological Bureau, made
an explanation on the draft law on prevention and alleviation of
seismological disasters at today's meeting.
</P>
<P>
The director said that China is a country frequently hit by
earthquakes, which often cause heavy losses. It should be noted
that the country has now entered a peak stage of the 5th active
earthquake period of the 20th century, he said, warning that it
possible that disastrous earthquakes measuring over 7 might occur.
</P>
<P>
"Prevention and alleviation of disasters caused by earthquakes
is a systematic project that affects all aspects of life and need
to be solved in a legal way," the director said.
</P>
<P>
At the today's meeting, lawmakers also heard reports on
international conventions and treaties on border disarmament, and
on judicial assistance between China and its peripheral countries.
</P>
<P>
During the five-day meeting, lawmakers will also review reports
on the implementation of the national economic and social development
plan since the beginning of this year and on the country's
meteorological work.
</P>
<P>
They will hear a report on the inspection of law enforcement of
product quality, and other relevant reports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
