<HEADLINE> Chinese Construction Firms Praised in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan Public Works and Housing
Minister Jonathan Ng'eno today praised Chinese construction firms
in Kenya for their high construction quality and very competitive
bidding prices.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Kenyan cooperation in this field should be deepened
through joint efforts in the future, Ng'eno said when meeting
with visiting Chinese Minister of Communications Huang Zhendong.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Road &AMP; Bridge Corporation, a leading company under
China's Ministry of Communications, has built roads with
first-level quality for the eastern African country, he
especially noted.
</P>
<P>
The corporation so far has constructed 198 kilometers of
roads, earning 2.3 billion Shillings (46 million U.S. Dollars
then) in total since it set up office here in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Ng'eno also spoke highly of China's long-term economic
assistance to Kenya, including the construction of a modern
stadium, a hospital and part of roads in the western areas.
</P>
<P>
The friendly relations between the two countries have been
greatly enhanced by the exchanges of visits of their top leaders,
he noted.
</P>
<P>
In response, Huang said Chinese construction firms in Kenya
will continue to focus themselves on the expansion of two-way
cooperation on the basis of being low-profitable, instead of
pursuing high profits.
</P>
<P>
Both China and Kenya are developing countries and should
develop their ties in the context of South-South cooperation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese firms play an active role in guaranteeing reasonable
bidding prices, creating jobs for local people, training local
skilled workers and engineers on Kenya's construction market,
Huang said. 
</P>
