<HEADLINE> South African Champions Suffers First Round Defeat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Former Africa club
champions Orlando Pirates suffered first round home defeat as the
first African Champions League kicked off this weekend.
</P>
<P>
Orlando Pirates of South Africa, conceding a late goal of their
home match, fell 2-1 against Premiero de Agosto from Angola.
</P>
<P>
Another former champions, Club Africain of Tunisia, were held
0-0 at home by Obuasi Goldfields of Ghana.
</P>
<P>
Zamalek of Egypt, winners of the African Champions Cup a record
four times, forced out a narrow 2-1 home win over Ferroviario of
Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
A dramatic North African showdown featuring USMA of Algeria and
Raja Casablanca of Morocco ended 2-2 with the Moroccans equalising
in injury time.
</P>
<P>
The Champions League replaces the long-running Champions Cup
and is the first African Football Confederation competition to
offer prize money and a round-robin format. 
</P>
