<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 300 Ugandan Civilians Killed Since Mid-June </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- More than 300 Ugandan civilians
have been killed in West Uganda since mid-June, a local newspaper
''The Monitor'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
About half of them were killed by the rebels of the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) at their gardens in search for food,
security sources told the paper.
</P>
<P>
The invasion of ADF rebels into Bundibugyo district in
mid-June caused an exodus to the neighbor district of Kabarole,
but lack of food forced some of the 80,000 displaced to return to
their home.
</P>
<P>
The refugees have to sell their goats at a price of 1,200
Uganda Shillings (some 1.2 U.S. dollars) a kilogram to collect
money for food, while the normal price in Kampala is some 2,800
Shillings a kilogram.
</P>
<P>
Many schools are closed in the district and the teachers and
children have fled their schools.
</P>
<P>
The Ugandan government army has killed some 120 rebels,
lossing 25 their own soldiers in the fightings against the rebels
so far.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group acting in western Kasese district. It
sent a team of rebels into Bundibugyo to develop a food source in
mid-June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
