<HEADLINE> Pak Port Offers Land to Develop Industrial Park </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Port Qasim Authority of
Pakistan will soon offer its 6,000 acres of land on competitive
basis through international bidding to develop it as an industrial
park.
</P>
<P>
Both domestic and foreign mega investors will be offered land
on either long-term lease or rental basis, according to Associated
Press of Pakistan (APP) today,
</P>
<P>
The investors are required to develop the land into four
special industrial zones measuring 1,500 acres each which are
located near Qasim port, the second largest port of Pakistan and
about 50 km southeast of the largest Karachi port.
</P>
<P>
The Port Qasim Authority (PQA) will provide the external
development around the park including connection to road and
railway network, beside provision of water and sewerage lines to
the industrial park.
</P>
<P>
The mega investor will be free to have his own state-of-the-art
planning for this special industrial zone according to the
requirement of potential investors or industrial plot holders, own
corporate management and provide civic amenities.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Communication has studied the proposal which
will be presented to the prime minister for final approval, APP
quoted PQA sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Once this concept is approved, PQA will go globally with the
help of the Board of Investment, Pakistani missions abroad, the
Ministry of Information and mass media to market this project
worldwide, the sources said.  
</P>
