<HEADLINE> Pak to Launch Drive Against Illegal Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan will launch a
campaign next month against vehicles which entered the country
illegally, official sources said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan Customs in collaboration with provincial excise and
taxation departments has finalized its preparations to launch the
campaign, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that an estimated 25,000 vehicles were
currently plying on the roads all over the country.
</P>
<P>
Most of such vehicles have got fake registration number plates
in connivance with the functionaries of provincial excise
departments, said the sources.
</P>
<P>
Due to non-payment of duties by these vehicles, the federal
government has been suffering loss of billions of rupees.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the provincial governments were also
suffering revenue loss of millions of rupees annually due to
non-payment of motor registration taxes by these illegal vehicles,
the sources said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
