<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Ends Slightly Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar closed
slightly lower against the U.S. currency, with the market
restrained by a lack of local data to provide direction.
</P>
<P>
The market was expected to be further subdued by the closure of
UK financial markets for a bank holiday tonight.
</P>
<P>
Rothschild Australia's Treasury Manager Paul Macarounas said
the foreign exchange market had been "seriously quiet today" and
he expected the Australian dollar to trade in a range of 74.60 to
74.90 U.S. cents tonight.
</P>
<P>
The local currency ended today in Sydney at 74.77 U.S. cents, a
little lower than its close last Friday of 74.90.
</P>
<P>
"There's still a short term bias toward pushing it up a little
higher," Macarounas said, adding that while the currency might not
hit 75,00 U.S. cents tonight, the figure was still reachable in
the short term.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 88.35 Japanese yen from 87.73
locally last Friday and against the German mark it was at 1.3596,
down from 1.3725. 
</P>
</TEXT>
