<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Meets With German Federal Assembly Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee,
meeting today with Antje Vollmer, vice-president of the German
Federal Assembly, said that China is pleased with the good
momentum in Sino-German relations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao described current Sino-German ties as "very good" and said
that frequent contacts between the two countries' leaders have
enhanced bilateral cooperative relations.
</P>
<P>
Sino-German links in the economy, culture, science, technology,
and education have been very "active" and have scored steady
growth, he said, pointing out that this year is the 25th
anniversary of the establishment of Sino-German diplomatic
relations.
</P>
<P>
The history of bilateral ties over the past 25 years has proven
that the principle of mutual respect, seeking common ground while
reserving difference, none-interference in each other's internal
affairs, equality and mutual benefit should always be observed in
dealing with state-to-state relations, Qiao noted.
</P>
<P>
China holds that it is understandable that there are different
views on some issues between states because of different
societies, economies, histories, culture, and traditions, Qiao
said, but that these differences should be settled through dialogue
on an equal footing and the promotion of mutual understanding.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the various parties in the German
Federal Assembly will view Sino-German ties from a strategic
point of view and work together to establish a long-term, stable
Sino-German relationship for the next century.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the German visitors will be
able to see more places in China and exchange more views with the
Chinese to gain a better understanding of China.
</P>
<P>
Vollmer told Qiao she has witnessed great changes in China over
the past 10 years and that co-operative relations are growing
rapidly. She added that the German Federal Assembly hopes to
increase its contacts with the NPC to make contributions to the
friendly ties between the two countries and two peoples.
</P>
<P>
Vollmer emphasized that dialogue and co-operation between the
parliaments of the two countries are in the interests of the two
peoples. No matter which party comes to power in Germany, the
policy of developing friendship and co-operation with China will
remain unchanged, she said.
</P>
<P>
Vollmer and her party are here as guests of the NPC Standing
Committee. They will travel on to Xi'an, Chengdu and Tibet.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
