<HEADLINE> Honduras Insist on Hosting Central American Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Sports officials of Honduras
reiterated on Sunday that the sixth Central American Games will go
ahead under the schedule from December 5 to 14 in San Pedro Sula,
a major industrial city in north Honduras.
</P>
<P>
The Organizing Committee categorically denied the rumors that
the games will either be cancelled or shifted to another city.
</P>
<P>
"Some of our old rivals are conspiring to oppose Honduras'
organizing of the Central American sports event," the committee
said.
</P>
<P>
Melesio Rivera of Salvador, president of the Central American
Sports Organization (CASO), expressed concerns on the slow pace of
the construction work after CASO representatives inspected the
sports facilities there last week.
</P>
<P>
He accused Honduras of concealing problems for a long time and
failing to fulfil the 6.3 million U.S. dollars budget promised by
the government.
</P>
<P>
Rivera said he will meet with Honduras president Carlos Roberto
Reina to discuss whether Honduras will continue to play hosts to
the event.
</P>
<P>
Honduras organizers rejected such criticism, insisting that all
the sports facilities will be completed before the opening of the
Games at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala has reportedly expressed its willingness to host the
games in case the CASO gives up Honduras. 
</P>
