<HEADLINE> Beijing Has 33,382 Shareholding Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 25 (Xinhua) -- China's capital has made
substantial progress in transforming state-owned enterprises into
shareholding ventures, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
Recent statistics show that the number of shareholding
enterprises in Beijing is 33,382, a rise of 20.48 percent from at
the end of last year. The enterprises have more than 63.9 billion
yuan in registered capital, up 13.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
As the shareholding system expands, direct financing through
the issue of shares has reached a new peak. So far this year, five
shareholding companies have issued shares on the domestic market,
raising 1.95 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
One enterprise has raised 327 million Hong Kong dollars by
issuing B-shares, which are reserved for overseas investors, and
another has raised more than 1.8 billion Hong Kong dollars by
floating shares in Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
