<P>
The money is expected to be used for recycling waste water and
establishing two sewage projects, South Korean Ambassador to
Jordan Jung-Il Oh was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
South Korean firms carrying out businesses in Jordan would be
employed in the projects, Oh added.
</P>
<P>
South Korea has moderate business exchange with Jordan; as now
its four major companies are involved in joint investment projects
with Jordanian firms in the fields of housing, irrigation and
industry.
</P>
<P>
Both countries are also planning to enhance cooperation in art
and tourism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
