<HEADLINE> Two Filipinos Killed as Rebels Attack Town Hall </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Some 100 rebels today attacked a
municipal hall and a nearby police station on Mindoro Island, the
central Philippines, killing two people.
</P>
<P>
Police said the New People's Army rebels barged into the town
hall after killing two security guards. Then they surrounded the
police station a few meters away and heavily fired from all
directions at the station.
</P>
<P>
The rebels withdrew after failing to pin down defending
policemen during the 10-minute gun battle, police said, adding
that the attack followed previous threats that the rebels would
raid police stations and town halls in southern Tagalog areas,
including Mindoro Island.
</P>
<P>
The specific reason of the attack was still unclear, police
said.
</P>
<P>
Negotiators of the New People's Army and the Philippine
government are holding peace talks in the Netherlands, saying they
would soon sign a peace agreement to end hostilities. 
</P>
