<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The seventh International Gem
and Jewelry Exhibition was opened here today for a four-day run.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lankan Export Development Board (SLEDB) and the National
Gem and Jewelry Authority are co-sponsoring the exhibition whose
objectives are to promote Sri Lanka as a source country for
quality gems and to expand the marketing activities and find new
buyers, the SLEDB sources to Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
This exhibition provides a showcase to the world proclaiming
Sri Lanka's finest resources and creativity in the field of gems
and jewelry, they said.
</P>
