T. Wickramratna and over 150 local and foreign buyers including
those from Australia, Japan, Tanzania and the United states
attended today's opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
About 130 booths of Sri Lanka's famous precious gem stones with
a few booths from abroad display goods at the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka was referred to as an "island of gem", and historical
evidence showed that gems were an important product of trade
during early times.
</P>
<P>
However, foreign exchange earned from gems export last year was
only one tenth of the total export earnings.  
</P>
