<HEADLINE> Tanzanian PM Urges Reduction of Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Tanzanians should not
regard poverty as part of their life and culture and should avoid
the notion that poverty must be with them for the rest of their
life, Prime Minister Frederick Sumaye has said.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while launching a book on poverty
reduction in Dodoma last weekend, according to a news dispatch
received here today.
</P>
<P>
Sumaye said, "each of us must refuse to harbor poverty and
start pursuing riches through hark work."
</P>
<P>
Tanzania is endowed with immense natural resources and it is
the responsibility of all Tanzanians to tap them to improve their
socio-economic status, said Sumaye.
</P>
<P>
He added that every able-bodied citizen has a chance of
becoming rich, provided they participate in gainful economic
activities instead of remaining mere spectators of development.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister noted that the country's sustainable
economic development relies squarely on Tanzanians and not
foreigners, therefore, it is necessary to educate Tanzanians to
stop thinking that only foreigners can become rich in the
country. 
</P>
