<HEADLINE> Colombian Government Begins New Talks With Guerrillas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
government and the guerrilla group "Colombian Revolutionary Armed
Forces" have begun a new round of dialogues in Mexico to prepare
for the upcoming peace negotiations, said Colombian Defense
Minister Gilberto Echeverry today.
</P>
<P>
Echeverry said the talks between government representatives and
guerrillas were just a beginning of a series of dialogues, which
aimed to make a time schedule for the peace negotiations.
</P>
