On Saturday, Colombian President Ernesto Samper Pizano
announced that his administration will open another non-military
zone to promote peace with the guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
The "Colombian Revolutionary Forces" has expressed willingness
for peace, he said.
</P>
<P>
Late last May, the Colombian government and the "Colombian
Revolutionary Forces" agreed to set up a non-military zone in the
southern part of the country, which resulted in the release of
dozens of government soldiers.
</P>
<P>
At the time, it was believed that the peace negotiations
between the government and the guerrillas could proceed with the
release. But it did not as expected. 
