<HEADLINE> Bomb Explosion Rocks Swedish Olympic Hopes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, August 25 (Xinhua) - A bomb exploded in a western
city of Gothenburg early on Monday, putting Sweden in danger in
its bidding to host the 2004 Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The blast with no one injuried at the Ullevi Stadium, was the
latest in a series of attacks against Swedish sports facilities,
apparently directed against the Sweden's Olympic bid.
</P>
<P>
All other attacks were reported in Stockholm, one of the five
finalists for the 2004 Olympic Summer Games. A decision on the
host city will be taken on September 5 in Lausanne, Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
The latest explosion took place at around 2.00 a.m. local time,
damaged the roof to a tunnel used by players to run onto the
sports arena.
</P>
<P>
The stadium has hosted the 1995 World Athletics Championships,
and was due to host the Olympic soccer competition should
Stockholm win its bid, said the the Stockholm Olympic Committee.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, a bomb wrecked the press section of
Stockholm's Olympic stadium but caused no injuries after a string
of arson attacks on the tennis and sports arenas in Stockholm.
</P>
<P>
Responsibility for those attacks was claimed by a group "We Who
Built Sweden". It has said hosting the Olympics would be a waste
of time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
