<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier, Singaporean President Meet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Singaporean President Ong Teng
Cheong and visiting Chinese Premier Li Peng applauded the
Singapore-China relations during their meeting here this morning.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to Li, Ong said he was very pleased to
meet again with Li, his old friend. He said his visit to many
Chinese provinces and cities had left him a deep impression.
</P>
<P>
China has scored a good yet fast development, with the economy
maintaining a quick increase and low inflation, he said, adding
the transportation and infrastructure have been greatly improved.
</P>
<P>
The president noted that China has great potential for
development and its future is very bright with its hardworking and
intelligent people.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Li Peng said he was glad to meet the
president and noted that Ong has always attached importance to
ties with China,
</P>
<P>
"We appreciate this very much," Li said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier said since the establishment of diplomatic
relations, the two countries treat each other in a cordial manner,
enjoy mutually beneficial cooperation in economy, and maintain
close consultation and cooperation in international and regional
issues.
</P>
<P>
China is satisfied with this, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
The China-Singapore relations is characterized by the frequent
exchange of visits between the bilateral leaders and the close
contacts at some international arenas, Li said.
</P>
<P>
This is of great importance in enhancing the mutual
understanding and trust, and in promoting the bilateral relations,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The premier said, "China attaches importance to developing the
Sino-Singaporean ties and regards this relationship as an
significant part of its good-neighborly friendship and cooperation
with Southeast Asia."
</P>
<P>
As the 21st century is drawing nearer, Li went on, both
countries should vision and promote the bilateral relations in a
historical and far-reaching perspective.
</P>
<P>
Ong said after China's resumption of exercise of sovereignty
over Hong Kong on July 1, all arrangements and operations are
going on smoothly, which has won praise worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Li said China will stick to its basic policy of "One Country,
Two Systems", "Hong Kong People Governing Hong Kong", and a high
degree of autonomy, thus a long-term prosperity and stability can
be maintained in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Li conveyed best wishes from Chinese President Jiang Zemin to
Ong, who in return asked Li to pass his best regards. On Jiang's
behalf, Li also invited Ong to visit China again, who accepted it
with pleasure.
</P>
<P>
Among those present at the meeting were He Chunlin, deputy
secretary general of the State Council; Liu Huaqiu, director of
the Foreign Affairs Office of the State Council; and Tang Jiaxuan,
vice foreign minister, who are all accompanying Li on the ongoing
visit.
</P>
<P>
Li is scheduled to hold talks with his Singaporean counterpart
Goh Chok Tong this afternoon and meet the local press later today.
He will meet Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew tomorrow.  
</P>
</TEXT>
