<HEADLINE> Italian Doctors Transplant Heart Without Blood Transfusion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Surgeons in Rome carried out a
heart transplantation without blood transfusion on Saturday night,
Italy's ANSA news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The patient was identified as Mirella Messina, 30, a member of
the Jehovah's Witness sect.
</P>
<P>
As the sect forbids blood transfusions, the operation team, led
by Professor Benedetto Marino, used techniques of recovering the
patient's own blood and blood dilution.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for the sect said more than 1,000 doctors in some
200 hospitals in Italy are now prepared to use similar techniques
when treating Witnesses.
</P>
<P>
Professor Marino conducted a similar heart transplanting
operation on a child member of the sect in 1986. 
</P>
</TEXT>
