<HEADLINE> Police Intercept Rare Animals to Be Smuggled to U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Peru's environment police today
discovered hundreds of rare Amazon jungle animals ready to be
smuggled to the United States, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Police are trying to track down the smugglers.
</P>
<P>
The animals were believed to have been brought from the
northern jungle city of Iquitos and were intended to be
transported to Los Angeles of the United States by Chilean airline
Lan Chile.
</P>
<P>
The destination was the U.S. aquarium company Tower Group, a
police officer said.
</P>
<P>
The animals, 787 in number, were stuffed into boxes. Nearly
half of them were found dead from suffocation in a storage hold
opposite Lima's international airport.
</P>
<P>
The animals rescued alive were taken to a Lima zoo. 
</P>
