<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Has More Telephone Subscribers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- East China's Zhejiang province
ranked third in the country at the end of July with a public
telephone exchange capacity of over 6.3 million lines.
</P>
<P>
The province is home to over five million telephone
subscribers, with an average 13.8 telephones per 100 people
representing a 1.96 percent rise on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The province's local telecommunications industry generated six
billion yuan in traffic volume for the January-July period, with
the sector's turnover volume ending the period at 5.6 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Hangzhou, the provincial capital, had more than 500,000
telephone users, double the figure for three years ago. The city
has an average 30.98 telephones for every 100 local residents, and
currently ranks fourth in the nation behind Haikou, Fuzhou and
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang plans to attach greater importance to the
installation of telephones in rural areas, and will extend
telephone lines to all local villages by the turn of the
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
