<HEADLINE> 10 Nepalese Die of Kalaazar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, August 25 (Xinhua) -- An outbreak of kalaazar has
claimed ten lives in Nepal, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Four victims were from Bara district of central Nepal, while
the rest came from Sarlahi district, about 60 kilometers east of
Bara.
</P>
<P>
The death toll could be much higher since people in Sarlahi
district are not accustomed to visiting hospitals, the reports
quoted hospital sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
A total of 31 patients are still taking medicine as the disease
is spreading to other villages in Sarlahi district.
</P>
<P>
Due to lack of equipment and medicine, the patients have to be
sent outside for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Villagers said mosquitoes had been spreading because
anti-mosquito insecticides had not been sprayed from time to time,
leading to the outbreak of kalaazar.  
</P>
</TEXT>
