<HEADLINE> Quake in Indonesia's Aceh Ruins Hundreds of Houses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- The tectonic earthquake which
hit central Aceh district, Indonesia, last Wednesday, damaged
hundreds of houses with a material loss of about 530,000 U.S.
dollars, Antara news agency today quoted an official as saying.
</P>
<P>
A number of people suffered slight and serious wounds, but so
far no casualties have been reported from the quake, measuring 5.8
on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman for the district administration said on Sunday
the natural disaster left nearly 60 families homeless and caused
minor damage to 200 houses, an elementary school building and a
public health service center.
</P>
<P>
Reports aid four villages in subdistricts of Linge and Isaq
located some 368 kilometers north of the provincial capital of
Banda Aceh were worst affected by the quake.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was located at 3.8 degrees latitude
and 96 degrees longitude.  
</P>
</TEXT>
