<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW -- Japanese Foreign Minister Yukihito Ikeda left here
for Paris Sunday after concluding his three-day official visit to
Poland. During his stay in Poland, he held talks with his Polish
counterpart, Dariusz Rosati, on bilateral ties and international
issues of common concern. (Poland-Japan-Visit)
