<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Uzbekistan Beat Yemen in Rescheduled Soccer Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Substitute Oleg Shatskikh scored
twice to pace Uzbekistan for a 5-1 win over Yemen in a rescheduled
soccer match in Tashkent, Uzbekistan on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
In the match originally scheduled for July, Uzbekistan that had
advanced already in the Asian first-round World Cup qualifiers,
opened its account in the 10th minute by Igor Shkvirin.
</P>
<P>
Omar Al-Ariki equalized 22 minutes later by netting in the sole
goal for Yemen, leaving the score tied at the half break.
</P>
<P>
Second half substitute Shatskikh scored the breaker in the 52nd
minute, Rovshan Bazarov added the third in the 62nd minute and
Shkvirin converted his second a minute later before Shatskikh
finished out the scoring in the 75th minute.
</P>
<P>
The game beared no consequence for either side as Uzbekistan
already had advanced to the second round and Yemen already had
been eliminated.
</P>
<P>
The game, initially scheduled for July 13, was canceled when
the Yemen team failed to show because of a strike by Yemen
transportation workers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
