<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, Indonesia Split Singles Titles in Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Sun Jun outwitted his
Indonesian peer to take the men's singles title while the women's
singles witnessed a reversed finish for the two countries at the
Badminton World Cup Championships in Yogyakarta on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun outlasted Indonesia's Joko Suprianto 15-9, 15-8 in 50
minutes, while Susi Sasanti of Indonesia took the women's crown by
beating Chinese Ye Zhaoying 11-8, 11-5 in merely 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
However, Ge Fei won a pair of doubles titles to give China
three out of the five crowns at the championships.
</P>
<P>
It was 22-year-old Sun's first victory over the nine-year-older
Suprianto in four tries, while Susi boasted of a 21-8 record
against the Chinese world champion who once led 8-7 in the first
set.
</P>
<P>
Ge Fei teammated with Gu Jun to beat compatriots Qin Yiyuan and
Tang Songshu 15-10, 9-15, 15-9 in an all-Chinese women's doubles
final, before paring with Liu Yong to claim the mixed double's
title.
</P>
<P>
Ge and Liu defeated Trikus and Minarti Timur of Indonesia,
12-15, 15-7, 15-10.
</P>
<P>
In the men's doubles, the host shuttlers Ricky Subagja and Rexi
Mainaki defeated the South Korean duo of Lee Dong-soo and Yeo
Yeng-sung 15-1, 10-15, 15-3.
</P>
<P>
The five-day tournament in Yogyakarta was the last world
championship as the International Badminton Federation will
reverse it to be a grand-slam system. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
