<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nine More Prisoners Killed in Inmate Clashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Nine more prisoners were killed
and seven seriously injured Saturday in Jamaican inmate clashes in
the capital of Kingston, pushing the death toll in recent prison
riots to 16, it is reported.
</P>
<P>
Twenty inmates have been injured in clashes since Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The clashes began Wednesday at the General Penitentiary in
Kingston and the St. Catherine District Prison in Spanish Town,
after the country's corrections commissioner said guards and
prisoners should be issued condoms.
</P>
<P>
Remarks of the commissioner, John Prescod, triggered a strike
of the security guards, who said Prescod's proposal implied that
they were having homosexual relations with the prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Prisoners took advantage of the strike and began to attack
fellow inmates. Inmates believed to be homosexuals were stabbed
and beaten to death or seriously injured, police said.
</P>
<P>
Prison guards returned to work and restored order with the help
of police and the military Saturday. Prescod had withdrawn his
proposal and said what he meant was only to prevent the spread of
AIDS. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
