<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia-Pacific Chief Justices Meet in Manila </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 25 (Xinhua) -- Chief justices and justice
ministers from Asia and Pacific gathered here today for a one-day
meeting to discuss legal and judicial reforms in the region.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, which is sponsored by the Asian Development
Bank (ADB), the delegates will discuss principal trends in legal
and judicial reforms in ADB members and relate these to the bank's
technical assistance to its members for such reforms.
</P>
<P>
The ADB-sponsored meeting is being held just one day before the
15th Conference of Law Association for Asia and Pacific and the
Seventh Conference of Chief Justices of Asia and Pacific, both
scheduled for August 26-31 in Manila.
</P>
<P>
Around 35 seminars on various topics of interests will be
conducted by legal experts at the law association meeting.
</P>
<P>
Some 30 chief justices from the Asia-Pacific countries and
regions will hold their meeting simultaneously to discuss
challenges of the judicial system, including judicial corruption,
case management and judicial education.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
