<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Moya Wins Hamlet Cup Tennis in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Fifth seed Carlos Moya of
Spain won his first ATP title of the season on Sunday by defeating
eighth seed Patrick Rafter of Australia 6-4, 7-6 (7-1) in the
303,000 U.S. dollars Hamlet Cup tennis tournament at Commack, New
York.
</P>
<P>
The 20-year-old Moya pocketed 43,000 dollars following his
career's third victory against Rafter.
</P>
<P>
Moya, who is to be seeded eighth at the upcoming U.S. Open this
week, improved his 1997 record to 47-20 by picking up his third
career ATP title after wins at Buenos Aires in 1995 and Umag,
Croatia last year.
</P>
<P>
The 24-year-old Rafter, seeded 13th at the Open, has not won a
tournament since taking his lone title at Manchester in 1994
despite his five-time outings to the tournament finals this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0283 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Schalken Defeats Rios in Pro Championship Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Sjeng Schalken of
the Netherlands beat second seed Marcelo Rios of Chile 7-5, 6-3 on
Sunday in the final of the inaugural 303,000 U.S. dollars MFS Pro
Championships in Boston.
</P>
<P>
Schalken, ranked 79th in the world, picked up his third career
ATP Tour title and first of the year after his victories at
Valencia, Spain in 1995 and Jakarta, Indonesia in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Schalken earned 43,000 U.S. dollars for today's victory.
</P>
<P>
It was the third upset set by the 20-year-old Schalken in as
many days in the tournament. Schalken completed a remarkable run,
knocking off top seed Alex Corretja of Spain in Friday's
quarter-finals before eliminating fifth seed Albert Costa of Spain
in Saturday's semifinals.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Rios, who fell to 46-20 this year, was playing
for his sixth career ATP Tour title and second this year.
</P>
<P>
He won his first at Monte Carlo in April and was a finalist at
the Italian Open and Marseille Open. Rios is seeded 10th at the
U.S. Open, which begins on Monday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
