The Age
</P>
<P>
-- Australia faces a crippling trade deficit of 46 billion
Australian dollars (34.5 billion US dollars) a year on computers,
software and information technology by 2005 unless the government
acts to develop the nation's information industries, a report to
the federal government warned Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- A one billion US dollar investment fund is being put
together to buy cheap commercial property from distressed sellers
in Thailand, with Australian investors set to be major
participants.  
</P>
</TEXT>
