<HEADLINE> Russians Win Men's Beach Volleyball Crown </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Russian pair of Dmitry Areshkin
and Edouard Senin won the international men's beach volleyball
tournament "Albena Challenger 1997" here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian duo outclassed Willi de Jesus Torres and Amori
Velasko of Puerto Rico 12-10, 10-12 and 12-10 for the title.
</P>
<P>
The third-place playoff was won by Brazil over Italy 15-9.
</P>
</TEXT>
