<HEADLINE> Three People Missing in Biplane Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 24 (Xinhua) -- A biplane believed to be
carrying three people has crashed off shore in Ocean City,
Maryland, today.
</P>
<P>
Police said the pilot and two female passengers were on board
the plane when it crashed near 94th street in the city.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Coast Guard and Maryland State Police divers are
searching for the victims.
</P>
<P>
Investigators from the Federal Aviation Administration and the
National Transportation Safety Board are en route to the crash
site. 
</P>
