<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Tourists Visit Croatia in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO, August 24 (Xinhua) -- Tourism has steadily begun to
recover in Croatia, with nearly a quarter increase in overnight
stays in July over the same period last year, according to the
Croatian Tourism Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Local press reports quoted officials of the ministry as saying
that there were 7.5 million overnight stays in Croatia during
July, which is about 23 percent more than in July of 1996.
However, the number of overnight stays is still 54 percent of the
pre-war 1990 level.
</P>
<P>
Split is the country with fastest recovery in tourism, as the
number of overnight stays in July is estimated to amount to 80
percent of the pre-war period.
</P>
<P>
Gorgana Borojevic, an assistant minister of the Tourism
Ministry, was quoted as saying that similar developments have been
noticed in August as well and if weather conditions continue to be
favorable, one could expect 9 to 9.5 million overnight stays for
this month.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is one of the mainstay industries of Croatia. The
Croatian government has predicted a 20 percent increase in the
number of overnight stays for the whole year although it means a
recovery only to little above half of the 1990 level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970825.0291 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Korea Sail into Soccer Semi-finals at Universiade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CATANIA, Sicily, August 24 (Xinhua) -- South Korea sailed into the
semi-finals of the Universiade soccer tournament after beating Brazil
2-1 at Cefalu on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The South Korean team, qualifying into the quarter-finals as group
runners-up, opened the scoring 9 minutes into the match when Kim Dae
Eui collected a loose ball in the area and beat the Brazilian goalie.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian levelled the score 1-1 at the 30th minute but their
hopes of taking the match into extra time were blown away by Kim Se In
who slamed home the winner at the 76th minute.
</P>
<P>
In other quarter-final matches on Sunday, hosts Italy trounced the
Netherlands 4-0, the United States blanked Ireland 5-0 while China's
youth team lost to Ukraine 2-0.
</P>
<P>
The semi-finals of the soccer tournament at the University Games
will be played on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
